        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8850.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Tyndall, 8 April [1873]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2357.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Joseph Dalton Hooker</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4839.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Tyndall</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3026.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Lubbock</ref>, and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_760.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Busk</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Lubbock was head of the bank <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4024.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Robarts, Lubbock &amp; Co</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">On the subscription for <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref>, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8843.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, [6 April 1873]</ref> and n. 2. See also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8872.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to T. H. Huxley, 23 April 1873</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1211.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Erasmus Alvey Darwin</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2306.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Archer Hirst</ref>.</note>
